[thinking] **Considering custom classloaders**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about the native image and its support for custom classloaders. There's a chance that it might not support unsupported dynamics. However, creating a simple subclass of ClassLoader could be a possibility. I'm wondering if it might fail since we don't load classes, but then I realize native image may not allow for runtime-defined classloaders. While Java supports it, the limitations in Native Image probably restrict custom classloaders, so maybe a subclass instance is allowed?
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Inspecting class loader behavior**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about whether I can set the loader. It seems like I can't. There’s a chance that using `ObjectUtil.defaultIfNull(classLoader, ClassUtil::getClassLoader)` in Hutool might help here. I'm curious if the implementation simply returns the object instead of a supplier when the object is null. I really need to take a closer look at this to understand it better!
