 image and its support for custom classloaders. There's a chance that it might not support unsupported dynamics. However, creating a simple subclass of ClassLoader could be a possibility. I'm wondering if it might fail since we don't load classes, but then I realize native image may not allow for runtime-defined classloaders. While Java supports it, the limitations in Native Image probably restrict custom classloaders, so maybe a subclass instance is allowed?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting class loader behavior**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether I can set the loader. It seems like I can't. There’s a chance that using `ObjectUtil.defaultIfNull(classLoader, ClassUtil::getClassLoader)` in Hutool might help here. I'm curious if the implementation simply returns the object instead of a supplier when the object is null. I really need to take a closer look at this to understand it better!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_tueQlH8cXkHVlXjlUynycUwD|fc_063166aa453cad640169f43885b290819ea177b1aaa65dc22c", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"defaultIfNull\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/cn.hutool/hutool-all/5.8.25/main/extracted/cn/hutool/core/util/ObjectUtil.java | head"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 568, "output": 1685, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21197, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777612906460, "responseId": "resp_063166aa453cad640169f4386b2ea0819eb22faae01a23450e"}}
