[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering custom classloaders**\n\nI'm thinking about the native image and its support for custom classloaders. There's a chance that it might not support unsupported dynamics. However, creating a simple subclass of ClassLoader could be a possibility. I'm wondering if it might fail since we don't load classes, but then I realize native image may not allow for runtime-defined classloaders. While Java supports it, the limitations in Native Image probably restrict custom classloaders, so maybe a subclass instance is allowed?\n\n**Inspecting class loader behavior**\n\nI’m thinking about whether I can set the loader. It seems like I can't. There’s a chance that using `ObjectUtil.defaultIfNull(classLoader, ClassUtil::getClassLoader)` in Hutool might help here. I'm curious if the implementation simply returns the object instead of a supplier when the object is null. I really need to take a closer look at this to understand it better!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_063166aa453cad640169f4386cd6c0819e9343b6e7135ef93c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9DiFtqq23r7c4j0e28edk25dyeS1sZzz-WiinfJfHyaT_sk8KqpuYPJI3ka074JH53AFI_TW_X2IO9WNSbCt7tPPDUbPwDCxAVV7E9GJk1hf820-CzfMMAalgRvAU8B5V50dvADtk9HPy6u-dXCy0QIn3TsX6LruFoVPipYlap_A21d7uZkGOoI0r8erDKPTj_q1xotO_0JHnFozkmic9ORPGTJ7RaT8qXVHPkaUSQD4Rw5uG8QN6Rwr8Qm9yY06A-3L7RVOWNZbWzXmspXptytcM30NCOZEMVsQJhVhrZ6jzZO0qXz24j2tgGm1ek59gyAqyHZbhoA7-maXjXO5TDuedmJae1UkP583n32rzRaay-GGx4SYI5hZjidxmJxpUfQbHIyrH6-1qxTZQmhyUv0KBlkEUYgLB-ukQD3FpmymNAQrfnWvi6eHdv2y7rnNVzR3ROddrWxfA7ctThfIjMgCg1BpDYlmBJEK2QQcypZhdxvrUILf6jZM7RElktu1GhmrWDM-2srfnoxLJfmbCnppNBSQYG6bxPw72hzPjp7-hg0YV2MWy0sa9lXw2KWyMspE_OvXPB6MQZyaKQt_QzMU8o3KczYcX1h79X5oHcLNh1WPSFOru_n4oIAfqnLdmjkS2q6m1yVvZEiBtVy5P6U33iP3Jd2kKFTQAH98hH8n-bea86ezmCOULznSnlr4qbrf73dWZy4AvYc4iFG-IbKkAjXMKsiY5MoTb_HYldKLMvoYAjndsUKm5CagSkAMsXqnSKSsW4u29cOvnNIVBSNrtkHvs3-a5Sd